1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Today we are going to look at how to export and import data from one WordPress website

2
00:00:05,720 --> 00:00:08,720
to another.

3
00:00:07,160 --> 00:00:10,160
To put it differently, you can use the Import and Export options to find a new house for

4
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:14,880
your content on WordPress.

5
00:00:14,760 --> 00:00:17,760
If you decide to export, your site's content is downloaded into an XML file that you can

6
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:23,560
then import to another WordPress site.

7
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:27,120
If you are ready to export, make your way to Tools and then click on Export.

8
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:33,440
Below Choose what to export, you can decide to export all content or only posts or only

9
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:39,120
pages or only media.

10
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:41,040
Let's select All content and then click on Download Export File.

11
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:49,200
And now we can go ahead and save the XML file to our computer.

12
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:55,160
This is a fresh installation of WordPress with no posts, no media and no pages.

13
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:07,720
And I would like to import the XML file from our previous site into this new site.

14
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:14,640
So make your way to Tools and click on Import.

15
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:19,960
And we are after the WordPress Importer right at the bottom.

16
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:25,440
So let's go ahead and click on Install Now.

17
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:29,480
And when it is installed successfully, we can click on Run Importer.

18
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:37,640
And now we can choose the XML file that we exported from our other website.

19
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:45,600
And then click on Upload File and Import.

20
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:52,040
To import media successfully, remember to select Download and Import File Attachments.

21
00:01:55,520 --> 00:01:58,520
Please also note, uattached media in the Media Library that has not been embedded into

22
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:03,120
a post or page will not be included in the XML export file.

23
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:08,240
Now we can go ahead and click Submit.

24
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:11,240
And this may take a few seconds.

25
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:15,080
And now we can go and check out everything that has been imported.

26
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:18,200
So let's make our way to Posts.

27
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:21,240
Here are all the posts from our other website.

28
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:25,040
All the media.

29
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:27,480
All the pages.

30
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:32,320
All the comments to posts.

31
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:35,680
And because it's the same theme, we can make our way to the Site Editor.

32
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
And we'll notice that our navigation menus, as well as our templates, and our header and

33
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:48,680
footer template parts have transferred over from the other website.

34
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:53,560
If the website you are importing to has a different theme than the one you are exporting

35
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:57,760
from, you will first need to install and activate the original theme on your new site.

36
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:04,520
Please note, when you transfer content to a new website, it does not include the site's

37
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,920
design, themes, or plugins.

38
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,000
But you can use a migration plugin for that if you were interested in transferring the

39
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:19,120
entire site.

40
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:22,040
When you go to Import, you would have noticed there are other systems you can import posts

41
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:26,440
or comments from, such as Blogger, Live Journal and even Tumblr.

42
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:30,520
There is also an option or plugin to convert existing categories to tags or vice versa.

43
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:37,520
I do hope you feel more comfortable now using the exporting and importing tool.

